<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aid Minister Resigns Over EU Membership Dispute </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aid Minister Resigns Over EU Membership Dispute </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2006122094 Paris AFP in English 1102 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2006122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Helsinki, June 20 (AFP) -- Finnish Aid Minister 
Toimi Kankaanniemi submitted his resignation Monday [20 June] to 
President Martti Ahtisaari after differences of opinion over 
Finland's European Union [EU] membership. 
  Prime Minister Esko Aho earlier Monday denied Kankaanniemi 
the right to vote against the government during a ballot to name 
representatives to sign the country's EU membership agreement 
this weekend in Corfu. 
  Kankaanniemi was the Christian Party's only representative 
in 
the government. It is not yet known whether the party will now 
leave the government or whether a new minister will be named. 

</TEXT>

