<H3> <TI>   Communist Party Revival Effort at Congress </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Communist Party Revival Effort at Congress </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P20885A Helsinki HUFVUDSTADSBLADET in Swedish 7 Jun 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> 94P20885A </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki HUFVUDSTADSBLADET </F>
<F P=105>  Swedish </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Finnish News Service report: "The Communist Party </F>
Reemerging in Fall"] 
  [Text] The Finnish Communist Party (Unity) (SKP-Y) is 
holding a congress in November where the purpose will be to 
resume the activity of the [former] Communist Party of Finland 
[SKP]. When in April the SKP-Y and the Left Alliance (VL) agreed 
to cooperate, it was asserted that the SKP's activity was being 
resumed. At the same time, agreement was reached that the VL 
would also place communists on its election lists in the next 
parliamentary election, states SKP-Y Chairman Yrjo Hakanen. 
According to Hakanen, communists will run in all election 
districts. Among the communist candidates, some will be members 
of the VL, some of the SKP-Y, and some unbound. 
  The convention will be held in Helsinki on 26 and 27 
November. Summoned to the convention are "all party units and 
district organizations within the SKP," in a statement released 
by the SKP-Y. 
  Some of the former minority [hard-line or Stalinist] 
communists are active within the SKP-Y. The SKP itself has been 
dissolved as an organization. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

