  [Excerpt] Gorel Thurdin is the new environment minister in 
Sweden, but in the future, all matters concerning the Oresund 
Bridge will be submitted to cabinet minister Reidunn Lauren. 
After giving its consent to the Oresund Bridge, the government 
is now leaving the matter to the Standing Committee on the 
Constitution and the water rights court, which will decide on 
the environmental conditions for building the bridge. The 
government will not discuss the bridge matter any more, cabinet 
minister Reidunn Lauren says. [passage omitted] 

