<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis Cites Prerequisites for Progress </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kliridhis Cites Prerequisites for Progress </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1906123994 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1906123994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis stressed that the 
prerequisite for any progress on the Cyprus issue is for the 
Security Council to be convinced that alternate ways should be 
adopted that would compel the Turkish side to show political 
will for a solution. 
  In an address at a gathering to commemorate the fallen EOKA 
[National Organization of Cypriot Fighters] fighters from 
Paphos, which was organized today by the town's fighter 
associations, President Kliridhis recalled that because of the 
lack of political will, which has also been noted by the United 
Nations, the National Council decided unanimously that the 
discussion of the confidence-building measures [CBM's] has been 
terminated and that we should proceed with discussions on the 
substance of the Cyprus issue after the necessary measures have 
been taken to break the Turkish intransigence. President 
Kliridhis also reiterated that he is prepared to sign an 
agreement on the CBM's provided the Turkish side accepts the 21 
March document. 
  The president added that the Greek Cypriots are united in 
the 
most crucial phase of our national problem and expressed the 
conviction that they will remain united in addressing it 
successfully. 
  Arriving at the ceremony, President Kliridhis said that he 
expects consultations on the Cyprus issue to continue in view of 
the Butrus-Ghali discussion. Responding to a question, he said 
that he has not yet received replies to his letters sent to the 
U.S. President and the British prime minister. Responding to 
another question, President Kliridhis said that he is not 
pessimistic. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

