<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] DISI [Democratic Rally] Chairman Ioannis Matsis 
said in London today that he carries a message from President 
Glavkos Kliridhis for German Chancellor Helmut Kohl related to 
Cyprus' application for accession to the EU [European Union]. 
The message will be conveyed to Chancellor Kohl during the 
European Popular Party meeting, which will take place tomorrow 
in Brussels and will be attended by leaders of European 
Christian Democratic parties. The meeting will deal with issues 
that will be raised during the EU Summit in Corfu on Friday [24 
June]. 
  Matsis, who went to London to attend a meeting of DISI's 
chapter in Britain, also said that Cyprus' effort for EU 
accession is the best possibility to promote the Cyprus issue in 
order to safeguard the safety of both communities and their 
human rights. 

