<H3> <TI>   Cetin Meets With EU Official on Relations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cetin Meets With EU Official on Relations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1606171294 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1610 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1606171294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, June 16 (A.A.) -- Hans van den Broek, who 
is responsible for the European Union's [EU] foreign relations, 
visited Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin on Thursday [16 June]. 
  Cetin, speaking during the meeting, said he was pleased to 
see van den Broek in Turkey, adding that Turkey's relations with 
the European Union will be discussed. 
  Cetin said Turkey and EU relations are going through an 
intense stage adding that decisions beyond the customs union 
should be taken. 
  The foreign minister also said Turkey and the EU have joint 
interest to several regional problems. "We will evaluate these 
problems," he added. 
  Van den Broek said the main reason of his visit is to show 
support to Turkey which is going through economic difficulties. 
  Recalling that this was his third visit to Turkey in 15 
months, van den Broek said this reflected close Turkish-EU 
relations. 

</TEXT>

