<F P=102>   TA1706184994 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1706184994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] It has been reported that Turkey and Iran support 
the achievement of a peaceful solution to the Karabakh issue as 
soon as possible. In addition, their determination to continue 
their cooperation on this issue was stressed. 
  The Foreign Ministry issued a statement noting that the 
Turkish and Iranian Foreign Ministries held technical 
consultations in Tehran on 13-15 June within the framework of an 
exchange of ideas on regional developments and issues. During 
these meetings, representatives of both countries expressed 
their views on the need for peace and stability to reign in the 
region and the need to achieve a solution of the Karabakh 
conflict through peaceful methods. 
  Stating that the territorial integrity of the countries of 
the region and the inviolability of their borders must be 
respected, the statement stresses that lasting solutions to 
disagreements cannot be achieved through the use of force and 
military coercion. 

