<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Major Step' Taken Toward Full WEU Membership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Major Step' Taken Toward Full WEU Membership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1806080394 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1806080394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Nevsehir deputy Esat Kiratlioglu and Adana deputy 
Selahattin Kilic returned to Turkey today after attending the 
40th session of the Western European Union [WEU] Assembly in 
Paris. 
  At a news conference at Istanbul Ataturk Airport on their 
return, the two deputies pointed out that two separate reports 
were drawn up to make three NATO member countries, including 
Turkey, full members of the WEU. Kiratlioglu pointed out that 
one of these reports was accepted. 
  [Begin Kiratlioglu recording] Turkey has taken a major step 
toward becoming a full member of the WEU. We believe that our 
association membership will be discussed and a conclusion will 
be reached in November. In the following stage, Turkey will be 
accepted as a full member of the WEU Assembly. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

