<H3> <TI>   Statistics Institute Issues Export-Import Data </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Statistics Institute Issues Export-Import Data </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1706155494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1706155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] It has been announced that exports increased by 2.4 
percent and imports decreased by 13.4 percent in the first four 
months of this year compared with the same period last year. 
  According to a statement issued by the State Statistics 
Institute, exports totaled $5,049,626,000 and imports reached 
$7,612,978,000 during January-April 1994. 
  A 69.1-percent decrease was registered in the foreign trade 
deficit in April 1994 compared with the previous year. The rate 
by which revenues from exports met the costs of imports also 
increased from 43.7 percent to 70.9 percent in the same period. 
  The foreign trade deficit for the first four months of the 
year diminished by 33.5 percent compared with the same period 
last year. The rate by which exports met imports in the same 
period also increased from 56.1 percent to 66.3 percent. 
  A comparison of the import-export figures for April 1993 and 
1994 shows that exports increased by 2.7 percent, while imports 
decreased by 40.1 percent. 

</TEXT>

