<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hopes To Convince RPF </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hopes To Convince RPF </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806164194 Brussels La Une Radio Network in French 1600 
GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1806164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels La Une Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] France is doing its best to convince the Rwandan 
Patriotic Front [RPF] of its good intentions. We asked French 
Foreign Minister Alain Juppe, who was in Cote d'Ivoire and 
Senegal to raise the issue of African support for this 
intervention, to comment on the issue: 
  [Begin Juppe recording] We have good arguments to convince 
the RPF. What are we planning to do in this operation? For 
example -- and I would say that this is the main aim of the 
operation -- we plan to go in to protect Tutsi civilians who are 
under threat of extermination in areas held by Rwandan 
[government] forces and militias. How can the RPF be hostile to 
such an operation, which aims to protect civilians? We have to 
explain what we plan to do. Perhaps there have been 
misunderstandings, perhaps what we planned was poorly 
understood. I am convinced that we can explain things and 
understand each other better. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

