<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Returns From UN, Washington, London </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Returns From UN, Washington, London </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1706213094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 2100 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1706213094 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis returned a 
short while ago from visits to the United Nations, Washington, 
and London where he discussed the situation unfolding in the 
Cyprus issue following the latest report by UN Secretary General 
Butrus Butrus- Ghali and the new contacts between the UN and 
[Turkish Cypriot Leader] Rauf Denktas. Foreign Minister 
Mikhailidhis presented a document to the UN secretary general in 
which the Cyprus Government calls on the permanent members of 
the UN Security Council to hold deliberations for a new 
beginning in the Cyprus issue through the investigation of new 
options. [passage omitted] 

