<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Does Not Rule Out Meeting With Turkey </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Does Not Rule Out Meeting With Turkey </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1706121794 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1130 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1706121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government Spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said the 
Greek Government does not rule out--at least theoretically--a 
meeting with the Turkish side, but clarified that what is 
important are the issues of discussion and the outcome, not the 
meeting itself. He stressed that the so-called Greek-Turkish 
disputes cannot be discussed, because the only thing separating 
the two countries is the continental shelf. Venizelos 
concluded: All the other differences are either violations or 
unilateral pursuits. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

