<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Rwanda: Western European Union To </F>
Hold Emergency Meeting"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Brussels, June 17 -- The permanent council of 
the Western European Union [WEU], the European Union's defence 
arm, will be meeting here this afternoon to discuss what 
European contribution can be made to UN peace operations in 
Rwanda. 
  Diplomatic sources said the meeting had been convened at 
Italy's and France's request. Yesterday, France said it was 
prepared to organise its own peace-making force to halt the 
massacres and protect civilians in Rwanda. 
  Italian diplomats were instructed to ask for an urgent 
session of the council on UN peace operations and humanitarian 
actions. The WEU includes all the EU nations except Denmark and 
Ireland. 

</TEXT>

