<H3> <TI>   EU Approves Aid for Italian Steel Firms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU Approves Aid for Italian Steel Firms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1606124994 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1836 GMT 15 
Jun 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1606124994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "European Union: Green Light for </F>
Italian Steel Aid"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Brussels, June 15 -- The European Commission 
today gave the go-ahead to 790 billion lire in aid for Italy to 
help 68 private steel firms make capacity cuts, breathing fresh 
life into an EU [European Union] steel plan that had seemed 
moribund. 
  EU Competition Commissioner Karel van Miert will illustrate 
the decision -- to be put to EU industry ministers on Wednesday 
[22 June] -- to Italian Industry Minister Vito Gnutti in Rome 
tomorrow. 
  EU Industry Commissioner Martin Bangemann said that "cutting 
5-6 million tonnes from Italy's private steel producers is the 
only chance we have to get up to the minimum European target of 
19 million tonnes, allowing us to apply the steel plan." 
  "Each of the 68 aid cases will have to be notified by Italy, 
and will be examined individually," van Miert said, underlining 
the need to "swiftly act on the Commission's June decision." 

</TEXT>

