<H3> <TI>   Bundeswehr To Hold Military Exercises in Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bundeswehr To Hold Military Exercises in Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1906185094 Hamburg DPA in German 1232 GMT 19 Jun 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1906185094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiel (DPA) -- Next year German soldiers will go to 
Russia for joint military exercises. In return, in 1996 Russian 
units are to train together with the Bundeswehr in western 
Germany, Defense Minister Volker Ruehe, Christian Democratic 
Union, said at the 100th Kiel Week on Saturday [18 June]. 
  "Europe is growing together best when people meet," Ruehe 
said. This also applies to the armed forces. Today Central 
Europe has the opportunity to become the anchor of stability for 
the entire continent. For this purpose, cooperation with Russia 
must be intensified. "Security and peace in Europe can be 
achieved only together with and not against Russia." At the 
same time, the minister announced that he will raise the number 
of reservists to such an extent that 100,000 of them can 
participate in exercises every year. 

</TEXT>

