<H3> <TI>   CSU Chairman Advocates Determined Opposition to PDS </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CSU Chairman Advocates Determined Opposition to PDS </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2006193894 Hamburg DPA in German 1447 GMT 20 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2006193894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Weimar (DPA) -- In the opinion of Christian Social 
Union [CSU] Chairman Theo Waigel, the Party of Democratic 
Socialism [PDS] has to be combated with the same determination 
as the extreme-right Republikaner. One cannot isolate Franz 
Schoenhuber as chairman of the Republikaner if other standards 
are applied to the PDS, Waigel said at the beginning of the 
annual conference of the chairmen of the Christian Democratic 
Union [CDU]/CSU Bundestag Group in Weimar on Monday [20 June]. 
  On 12 June, the successor party of the Socialist Unity Party 
of Germany established itself as the third political power in 
the new laender and gained between 15 and above 20 percent of 
the votes. Waigel now calls for an increased confrontation with 
the parties on the left and the right fringe. 
  The FRG finance minister assessed as a good sign the fact 
that, for the first time, the new laender's need for transfer 
payments will not further increase next year. In the first 
quarter of this year, a growth rate of 10 percent was achieved 
in eastern Germany. It still cannot be said how long the 
recovery process will take. However, the upswing has obviously 
begun, he said. 

</TEXT>

