<H3> <TI>   PLO Preparing To Open Office in Vatican </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO Preparing To Open Office in Vatican </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2006131394 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1445 GMT 18 
Jun 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2006131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "PLO To Open Office for Relations </F>
With Holy See"] 
  [Excerpt] Vatican City, June 18 -- The Palestine Liberation 
Organization is preparing to open an office for relations with 
the Vatican "in a matter of weeks," Nimr Hammad, the Palestinian 
general delegate in Italy confirmed today. 
  Hammad said Vatican and Palestinian officials are now 
"discussing the test of an agreement for mutual recognition" in 
a statement given to the Italian news agency ANSA. The opening 
of a Palestinian office for relations with the Holy See would 
appear to sanction the start-up of official relations between 
the two sides. 
  On this score, Palestinian sources here have recently 
referred to the prospect for imminent "diplomatic relations." 
The feasibility of this step, however, is clouded by what the 
Vatican itself describes as "the beginning of Palestinian 
autonomous government responsibility in the Gaza region and the 
city of Jerico," in relation to full diplomatic recognition, 
with an exchange of ambassadors, with an entity which is not yet 
a full-blow state. 
  In any case, noted Vatican watchers, a Palestinian 
"presence" 
in the Vatican would certainly come as a step in this direction 
and help confirm the desire of the Holy See to play a role in 
the Middle East peace process. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

