<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Martino Sees Greater Role for </F>
Cultural Policy"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, June 15 -- Italian Foreign Minister 
Antonio Martino said here today that he sees a greater role for 
cultural affairs in Italian foreign policy. 
  Addressing a session of the National Committee for the 
Promotion of Italian Culture Abroad at the Foreign Ministry, he 
said the new policy would strive to give greater stress to 
interactions between science, technology, economics, political 
science and culture. 
  According to Martino, in this perspective, the promotion of 
culture would be an important factor in lending credibility to 
Italian activity on the international stage. 
  He also said this would mean giving the Foreign Ministry the 
appropriate tools and means for achieving the target in which he 
said he expects the committee to produce concrete and 
appropriate proposals in the very near future. 

