<H3> <TI>   Wuerfel To Head FDP's EU Liaison Office </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wuerfel To Head FDP's EU Liaison Office </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2106112894 Munich FOCUS in German 20 Jun 94 p 11 </F>
<F P=103> AU2106112894 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich FOCUS </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Safe Seats"] </F>
  [Excerpt] The Free Democratic Party of Germany [FDP] is 
looking after its ladies. Uta Wuerfel, top candidate who failed 
in the European elections, is going to Brussels, even without a 
mandate. She will become head of the FDP liaison office with the 
European Union Commission and the European Parliament. This 
should take care of her worries that she might have to stay at 
home and do nothing. 
  Ursula Seiler-Albring, state minister (parliamentary state 
secretary) in FDP Chairman Kinkel's Foreign Ministry, will be 
given a post as ambassador, probably in Vienna. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

