<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Eastern Industry Provides 2 Percent of 1993 Exports </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Eastern Industry Provides 2 Percent of 1993 Exports </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106085394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0821 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2106085394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Wiesbaden (DDP/ADN) -- Industry in the former GDR 
only contributed 2 percent to total German exports last year. 
At 12 billion marks, exports only reached 30 percent of 1989's 
level, the Federal Statistical Office announced in Wiesbaden 
today. 
  The office said the political and economic changes in the 
former Eastern Bloc states were responsible for the fall in 
exports. Exports to these countries had dropped to 20 percent of 
the level of 1989 but still made up 52 percent of eastern German 
exports. 

</TEXT>

