<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Eduskunta has approved the second supplementary 
budget this year, intended mainly to alleviate youth 
unemployment. The supplementary budget, totaling 1.36 billion 
Finnish markkas [FMk], was approved on the strength of votes 
from the government side, with proposed addendums by the 
opposition being rejected. With this supplementary budget the 
state's total revenue and spending this year approach FMk200 
billion. 

</TEXT>

