<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meets Prime Minister Ciller </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets Prime Minister Ciller </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2006164594 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1615 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2006164594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, June 20 (A.A) -- Prime Minister Tansu 
Ciller on Monday [20 June] met with Turkmenistan President 
Saparmurad Niyazov, currently in Turkey on an official visit. 
  She said during the meeting that Turkey and Turkmenistan 
share common cultural and historical ties and have good 
relations, adding that efforts should be made to take them even 
further. 
  She said that Eximbank opened a credit line of 90 million 
dollars to the republic to develop trade between the two 
countries, and 10 million have not yet been used, adding further 
requests could be met with pleasure. 
  She said that there are about three thousand Turkmen 
students 
studying in Turkey adding that both countries should develop 
relations and cooperation in all fields. 
  Niyazov's talks in Turkey are expected to focus on possible 
joint projects to develop and operate the Central Asian 
Republic's major natural gas reserves and construction of a 
pipeline to export Turkmen gas to Europe across Turkey. 
  Turkey's bilateral trade with the republic rose to 160 
million dollars last year from 28 millions in 1992. 

</TEXT>

