<H3> <TI>   Court Order Places DEP Deputies `Under Surveillance' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Court Order Places DEP Deputies `Under Surveillance' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2006153494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1200 
GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2006153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] Nusrettin Demiral, chief prosecutor of the Ankara 
State Security Court, has given the order to place under 
surveillance the Democracy Party [DEP] deputies whose 
deputyships were terminated in the wake of a decision made by 
the Constitutional Court. Six of the DEP deputies whose 
deputyships were terminated are abroad and two are in Ankara. 
Another five deputies whose immunities were lifted by the 
Assembly in March are being detained in the Ankara Central 
Penitentiary. 
  Answering Turkish Radio and Television correspondent's 
questions, Demiral said that he gave the order to place under 
surveillance two of the deputies in Ankara as well as six 
deputies, currently abroad, in case they return to Turkey. 
Demiral announced that he could not give additional information 
on the duration of the surveillance. 
  The DEP deputies who are currently abroad are as follows: 
Ali Yigit, Mahmut Kilinc, Zubeyir Aydar, Remzi Kartal, Naif 
Gunes, and Nizamettin Toguc. Selim Sadak and Sedat Yurtdas are 
at this moment in the Turkish Grand National Assembly. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

