<H3> <TI>   Deputies Refuse To Leave Parliament </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputies Refuse To Leave Parliament </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2006155094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1440 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2006155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, June 20 (A.A) -- Sedat Yurtdas, expelled 
from Parliament last Thursday [16 June], said today that they 
will not leave the Parliament building, because of the order 
given by the chief prosecutor to detain them. 
  As the Constitutional Court last Thursday decided to ban the 
Democracy Party [DEP] and strip its 13 members from Parliament 
membership, Ankara State Security Court Chief Prosecutor Nusret 
Demiral ordered the detention of Sedat Yurtdas and Selim Sadak, 
the two remaining DEP members. 
  After learning that they will be detained, the two deputies 
received a call from Deputy Parliament Speaker Kamer Genc who 
told them that he will not allow the police to enter the 
premises and will take action before the High Board of Judges 
and Prosecutors to protect the deputies. 
  He added that Parliament Speaker Husamettin Cindoruk and 
Demiral disagreed on their detention. 

</TEXT>

