<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mentese: PKK `Desperate'; Leader `Inciting' Men </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mentese: PKK `Desperate'; Leader `Inciting' Men </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2006194294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2006194294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Interior Minister Nahit Mentese has said that the 
PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] is desperate and for this 
reason they are attempting bombings in cities. On a study tour 
in Yalova, Mentese discussed the issue of terrorism at a meeting 
he held with citizens. 
  [Begin Mentese recording] PKK leader Apo [Abdullah Ocalan] 
is continuously inciting his followers and his men. He is 
inciting them on the radio with his messages. He is saying: Go 
and plant bombs at tourist sites. Go and cause disturbances in 
Istanbul, Izmir, and Ankara. Aim at big cities. Apo is 
avoiding engagement because he is losing considerably in the 
southeast. We are taking every measure necessary. We are ready 
and thanks to our intelligence we are capable of capturing the 
terrorists. As you can see we capture terrorists everyday but 
our people should also assist us and they should also be 
careful. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

