<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Some of the views of the IBDA-C </F>
[Islamic Great Eastern Raiders Front"]] 
  [Text] Secularism: "We are against the concept of 
secularism in Turkey. We believe that it has no historical or 
ideological basis within Turkish culture. No other state is so 
afraid of its own people. It exerted special efforts to implant 
the notion of discrimination between Islam and canonical law in 
the minds of the people. The Ataturk revolution was against 
Islam. That is why we question it." 
  The United States: "The United States is afraid of radical 
Muslims and is searching for moderate Muslims to act as its 
agents. This is its concession to the Muslims." 
  Fethullah Gulen: "He is a volunteer agent of the secular 
front." 
  Great Unity Party [GUP]: "The fact that its grass roots are 
Muslim obliges the GUP to adopt an anti-Kemalist stand or at 
least show that it is not Kemalist. All it has done so far is 
to pursue a contrived policy that wavers between Kemalism and so 
called anti-Kemalism." 
  Turkish-Islamic synthesis: "Our ideological relations with 
the Intellectuals Hearth are not good at all. We are against 
such things as the Idealist movement and Turkish-Islamic 
synthesis. One cannot combine Turkish nationalism and Islam. 
Islam comes first." 
  The Kurdish issue: "Islam does not interfere in the customs 
and traditions of any race, religion, or language. It gives 
them freedom. The Kurdish problem is a regional issue." 

</TEXT>

