<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Klestil Meets With Arab League Secretary General </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Klestil Meets With Arab League Secretary General </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1906114594 Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG in German 18 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1906114594 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "The President Received"] </F>
  [Text] For Arab League Secretary General 'Ismat 'Abd 
al-Majid the result of the Austrian referendum on European Union 
[EU] membership is "a massive boost for Austria's role and 
importance in the world." During a meeting with President 
Thomas Klestil in Vienna's Hofburg Palace, he said that by 
clearly saying yes to a larger Europe Austria "has regained 
that central position which the country had assumed for 
centuries." The Arab and the Islamic world is pleased about the 
result of the Austrian EU referendum also because it knows that 
it now has one more close and trustworthy friend in the EU. 
President Thomas Klestil, who a few hours before had received 
the OPEC ministers who are meeting in Vienna, expressed his 
conviction that Austria's opinion and advice in the EU will be 
in particularly high demand in the future when the cooperation 
of the EU with East Europe, but also with the Middle East, will 
be the issue. Since the time of [former Austrian Chancellor] 
Bruno Kreisky, Austria's special closeness with the Arab world 
has been known and appreciated. In the meeting with the Arab 
League secretary general President Klestil discussed, among 
other things, current developments in Bosnia, the Middle East 
peace process, and political and social development in Africa. 
'Ismat 'Abd al-Majid, who is in Vienna to visit the UN 
organizations, was accompanied by Arab League Deputy Secretary 
General Ahmed Adel and Arab League representative in Austria 
Samir Hezzah [preceding two Arab names spelling as published]. 

</TEXT>

