<H3> <TI>   Military Mission Arrives in Zaire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Mission Arrives in Zaire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106095494 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 0900 
GMT 21 jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106095494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A French military mission arrived yesterday in the 
eastern Zairian town of Goma, near the Rwandan border, to assess 
under what conditions a force intervening in Rwanda could 
transit through Zaire. 
  A representative of the Rwandan Patriotic Front [RPF] is 
expected in Paris today. He will meet French leading officials. 
This was announced by Cooperation Minister Michel Roussin in a 
radio interview earlier today. 

