<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Singapore Airlines Orders 10 Airbus Planes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Singapore Airlines Orders 10 Airbus Planes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2206114294 Paris AFP in English 1105 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2206114294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Paris, June 22 (AFP) -- Singapore Airlines ordered 
10 more A340-300 long-range Airbus planes and took out options 
for another 20 on Wednesday [22 June], the European consortium 
Airbus Industrie announced. 
  The total order for the 30 planes would be worth 5.4 billion 
dollars. 
  The airline, which already ordered seven A340's in December 
1992, will thus become Airbus Industrie's biggest customer with 
37 of this very long-range model. 
  The planes ordered Wednesday will be delivered starting in 
spring 1996. 

</TEXT>

