<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   United Greens Elect New Chairman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    United Greens Elect New Chairman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2006102494 Vienna DIE PRESSE in German 20 Jun 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> AU2006102494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Adi Pinter New Chairman of United </F>
Greens"] 
  [Text] Adi Pinter, a former soccer coach, was elected 
chairman of the United Greens by the national assembly of the 
United Greens on Sunday [19 June]. He received 70 percent of 
the votes, thus defeating the Vienna biologist Gerhard 
Pretzmann. Pinter, who is succeeding Josef Buchner after 
internal differences, has spoken against the ratification of the 
European Union treaty in parliament. 

</TEXT>

