<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abu Dhabi Purchases 20 Percent of OeMV </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abu Dhabi Purchases 20 Percent of OeMV </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2106142594 Vienna DIE PRESSE in German 21 Jun 94 p 13 </F>
<F P=103> AU2106142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Agreement With Abu Dhabi Finalized"] </F>
  [Text] Transportation Minister Viktor Klima formally 
finalized the participation of Abu Dhabi's state-owned 
International Petroleum Investment Company (IPIC) in the 
Austrian Petroleum Corporation (OeMV) in Abu Dhabi at the 
weekend. IPIC has bought 19.56 percent of the basic capital of 
the petroleum company (2.7 billion schillings). 
  Beyond specific cooperation, Austria is viewed as an "ideal 
partner state in Europe" by the United Arab Emirates, the 
transportation minister told APA after his brief visit to Abu 
Dhabi. Sales cooperation thus applies to Central Europe as a 
whole. However, OeMV will continue to operate independently. 
  Also, there is "neither an obligation nor the intention" on 
the part of the Arab partner to introduce its own gasoline brand 
into Central Europe. Klima also ruled out splitting the 
department responsible for natural gas deals from the concern. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

