<H3> <TI>   Algerian Prime Minister Arrives, Meets Dehaene </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Algerian Prime Minister Arrives, Meets Dehaene </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106210994 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106210994 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Prime Minister Mokdad Sifi and the delegation 
accompanying him arrived in Brussels today. Soon after his 
arrival, he held preliminary talks with Belgian officials and 
representatives of our community there. Over to Rachida Hamadi 
from Brussels: 
  [Hamadi] Indeed. Prime Minister Mokdad Sifi and the 
delegation accompanying him are now continuing their meeting 
with our community in Belgium at the Algerian embassy. Mr. 
Mokdad Sifi arrived in Belgium at noon today. He met Arab 
ambassadors and held his expected meeting with Belgian Prime 
Minister Jean-Luc Dehaene. The meeting lasted over one hour. 
Mr. Dehaene is tipped as the candidate to succeed Jacques 
Delors as president of the European Commission. 
  [Begin Dehaene recording in French with superimposed Arabic 
translation] Relations between Belgium and Algeria have always 
been good; there have been constant commercial and economic 
links. This meeting falls within the framework of efforts aimed 
at strengthening these relations. [end recording] 
  [Hamadi] The purpose of this European tour, which comes on 
the eve of the European summit in Corfu and less than one month 
before the G-7 summit in Naples, is to bolster European-Algerian 
cooperation in various fields, particularly after the agreement 
with the IMF and the Paris Club. Observers here point out that 
Algeria has invigorated the political and economic reforms by 
establishing the Transitional National Council and the National 
Economic and Social Council, and has opened the first door to a 
market economy. They add that all these facts will give Algeria 
a winning card in its international economic dealings. 
  [Begin Sifi recording] The visit has several objectives. We 
will be disseminating information that will enable us to explain 
the Algerian Government's efforts in the political and economic 
fields. This visit is also aimed at developing and bolstering 
support in the political and economic fields. [end recording] 
[passage omitted] 
  The prime minister will leave Belgium tomorrow for Paris on 
a 
similar mission. 

</TEXT>

