<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Favors UN Force in Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Favors UN Force in Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2206090994 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 0830 GMT 
22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2206090994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hilversum Radio Netherlands </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Dutch Defense Minister Relus ter Beek has said 
he wants the UN Security Council decision to send a 5,500 strong 
force of African troops to Rwanda to be given preference over 
the French plan to send its own force to the African country. 
Mr. ter Beek's statement follows talks between him and the UN 
Secretary General Dr. Butrus Butrus Ghali in New York. Mr. ter 
Beek said he was not opposed to the French plan, but he 
preferred the option of a UN force because of the credibility 
the UN has. The UN Security Council has just been meeting to 
discuss the French plan to send a military force to Rwanda, but 
no decision is expected until later today. 

</TEXT>

