  [Text] One hundred and forty six men belonging to the 
second foreign paratroopers regiment abroad have left Calvi [in 
Corsica] to relieve troops in Gabon. They may intervene in 
Rwanda from there if the need arises. Indeed, they may be some 
of the first French soldiers sent to that country should there 
be a French intervention. 

