<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delors Matches Balladur in Presidential Poll </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delors Matches Balladur in Presidential Poll </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2106145794 Paris LA TRIBUNE DESFOSSES in French 21 Jun 94 
p 31 </F>

<F P=103> BR2106145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LA TRIBUNE DESFOSSES </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Presidential Election: </F>
Balladur-Delors: Identical Approval Ratings"] 
  [Text] According to a CSA [expansion unknown]-LE PARISIEN 
opinion poll, 47 percent of French people would have confidence 
in Jacques Delors "as president of the Republic" (up 4 percent 
in a month), in other words a confidence rating almost identical 
to that of Edouard Balladur who, with 48 percent, is down 1 
percent. Philippe de Villiers shows the biggest increase (up 13 
percent) at 22 percent and comes in 11th place, just ahead of 
Michel Rocard, down 7 percent to 21 percent (the opinion poll 
was carried out before his resignation [as Socialist Party 
leader]). Jacques Chirac is in third position with 38 percent 
(down 2 percent), ahead of Simone Veil and Raymond Barre, who 
both have 34 percent. Then come Bernard Kouchner at 29 percent 
(down 1 percent), Jack Lang at 29 percent (down 3 percent), 
Charles Pasqua at 29 percent (down 6 percent), Valery Giscard 
d'Estaing at 26 percent (up 2 percent), Francois Leotard at 24 
percent (down 4 percent), and Philippe Seguin at 23 percent 
(down 4 percent). 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

