<H3> <TI>   Leotard Speaks Out in Favor of Nuclear Testing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leotard Speaks Out in Favor of Nuclear Testing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2006115994 Paris LE MONDE in French 17 Jun 94 p 9 </F>
<F P=103> BR2006115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LE MONDE </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "F.B.": "Military Programming Law Adopted -- </F>
Mr. Leotard Declares France Cannot Be Exempted From Nuclear 
Testing"] 
  [Excerpts] On Wednesday, 15 June, the Senate passed the 
1995-2000 Military Programming Law submitted by Defense Minister 
Francois Leotard. [passage omitted] 
  Several senators are worried about the nuclear deterrence 
issue, which has been a subject of contention between the 
president of the Republic and the government. Mr. de Villepin 
expressed doubts as to the "realism of the determination to 
implement" the nuclear program "without additional testing." 
Mr. Leotard demonstrated complete agreement, indicating that 
"test simulations will not be sufficient to exempt France from 
actually performing additional testing." "Not a single 
scientist or member of the scientific community ever told me 
otherwise," he added. 

</TEXT>

