BFN 

  [Text] It is being reported from the UN Headquarters that 
in letters to President Glavkos Kliridhis and Turkish Cypriot 
leader Rauf Denktas, UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali 
will stress that the 21 March UN document is the final method to 
implement the confidence-building measures, and will clarify the 
points that were discussed with Denktas last week. This 
information was included in a report from the REUTERS News 
Agency, citing diplomats at the UN Headquarters. According to 
the same report, Butrus-Ghali hopes that his letters will help 
both sides to finally accept the confidence-building measures. 
  The Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation correspondent reported 
from New York that either Joe Clark, the UN secretary general's 
special representative in Cyprus, or Alternate UN Secretary 
General Marrack Goulding, is expected to convey the letters to 
Kliridhis and Denktas next week. 
  Government Spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis said the government 
has no official information that the UN secretary general 
intends to send letters to Kliridhis and Denktas. 

