<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Promote Cyprus Issue at EU Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Promote Cyprus Issue at EU Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2106170594 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1500 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2106170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government Spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis confirmed 
that the government has sent letters to the leaders of the 
twelve European Union [EU] member states regarding the EU summit 
in Corfu. Kasoulidhis did not reveal the contents of the 
letters. 
  On Thursday evening [23 June], President Glavkos Kliridhis 
will meet Greek Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou in the 
presence of European Commission President Jacques Delors on the 
sidelines of the EU summit, which will begin on Friday. 
Kliridhis will also meet British Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd 
at the latter's request. 
  The government spokesman said the government's efforts in 
Corfu will focus on promoting Cypriot positions on political 
issues and also on the reasons why the Corfu summit must take a 
step forward in Cyprus' EU membership application. 
  The president will leave for Corfu tomorrow afternoon. 
Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis, the government spokesman, 
and other officials will accompany him. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

