<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Denktas: Draft Agreement Prepared on Cyprus </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2106152994 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1500 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2106152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lefkose, June 21 (A.A.) -- Turkish Republic of 
Northern Cyprus [TRNC] President Rauf Denktas said on Tuesday 
[21 June] that his country has prepared a draft agreement of the 
UN proposed confidence-building measures. 
  Denktas speaking to the Anatolian Agency said he discussed 
the draft agreement together with Foreign Ministry Deputy Under 
Secretary Tugay Ulucevik and head of Cyprus-Greece desk Ertugrul 
Apakan. 
  He said TRNC always conveyed that it has the political will 
to reach an agreement adding that Greek Cypriot leader Glavkos 
Kliridhis did not want an agreement to reach a lasting solution 
for the Cyprus problem. 
  Denktas said TRNC will always stand still and continue its 
struggle until the end. 

