<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Ankara, June 21 (A.A.) -- Former Democracy Party 
(DEP) deputies Sedat Yurtdas and Selim Sadak left parliament 
premises at 2:05 pm., it was reported on Tuesday [21 June]. 
  Yurtdas and Sadak stayed at parliament premises as Chief 
Prosecutor Nusret Demiral ordered their detention on Monday. 
  Later the two deputies said they will leave parliament after 
Acting Parliament Speaker Kamer Genc said that the parliament 
memberships of Sedat Yurtdas and Selim Sadak will continue until 
the Constitution Court decision is published in the OFFICIAL 
GAZETTE [passage omitted]. 

