<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Seek Death Penalty for 8 DEP Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Seek Death Penalty for 8 DEP Members </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2106150594 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1440 GMT 21 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2106150594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, June 21 (A.A.) -- Ankara State Security 
Court Chief Prosecutor Nusret Demiral said on Tuesday [21 June] 
that former Democracy Party (DEP) members Selim Sadak and Sedat 
Yurtdas will be taken into custody if they leave the Parliament. 
  Demiral told reporters that eight former DEP deputies will 
not be judged at the same time with other DEP members who were 
earlier detained adding that another indictment will be prepared 
for these eight. 
  Demiral said they will seek the death penalty for these 
eight 
according to the Constitutional Article 125 as they earlier did 
to five DEP and one independent deputies who were earlier 
detained. 
  Article 125 says `an attempt to endanger the territorial 
integrity and future of the state will be punishable by death.' 

</TEXT>

