<F P=100> CANADA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ouellet Announces 350 Troops To Be Sent to Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ouellet Announces 350 Troops To Be Sent to Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2106205994 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 
2030 21 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2106205994 </F>
<F P=104>  Montreal Radio Canada International </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Canada is sending 350 peacekeepers to Rwanda. The 
foreign affairs minister, Andre Ouellet, made the announcement 
in Ottawa today. The Canadians are communications specialists 
and they will be a part of the 4,000 member force the United 
Nations is putting together. Mr. Ouellet says the Canadians 
will leave for Rwanda within a few weeks. They'll join 11 other 
Canadian officers already serving with the UN contingent in 
Rwanda. 

</TEXT>

